    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Makes sense, I didn't think of all those use-cases.\n\nNot sure on the naming `onDomNodeAdded`, this feels really low level. Why not `onRender` to stay consistent with our naming of events? It could still pass the DOM node and data to the function, just maybe not add a mention of \"adding a DOM node to the DOM tree\" in the naming.\n",
