    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Here's a render method, please do some DOM and send it back to us\n\nYou mean, like the `template` method? ;)\n\nMaybe we can allow the `template` method to return a DOM element instead of a string. That way we can bind any event with any data to hit easily. That would be really straightforward.\n\nNot sure about memory leaks and garbage collecting of that, but otherwise this feels like the easiest API.\n",
    "created_at": "2016-06-06T17:30:19Z",
